Looking at the balance sheet, these types of assets are typically classified as "Fixed Assets" or "Property, Plant and Equipment". Fixed assets are tangible items used in operations over multiple periods.

In the provided balance sheet, I can see:
- "Fixed Assets" with an initial amount of 5000000.00 as of 2023-12-31
- "Fixed Assets" with an end amount of 5676195.87 as of 2024-01-27

This is exactly what I'm looking for - tangible items held for operational use. The "Fixed Assets" line item represents the property, plant, and equipment used in the business.
